news.title: Bengaluru civic body set to collect Rs 26 crore as e-khata costs Rs 125
news.para: The breakdown of this cost is as follows: Rs 125 to Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP) for issuing the e-khata, Rs 45 as service fee to the Bangalore One centre, and an extra Rs 5 per page for scanning documents, which includes absolute sale deed and half-a-dozen other important papers.

news.title: Mumbai: Citizens oppose auction of BMC property in Malabar Hill
news.para: Citizens stated that the property card of the plot shows it is vested with BMC for a public garden.

news.title: Tamil Nadu's registration department revenue rises by Rs 1,222 crore after revised property guidelines
news.para: According to officials from the registration department, revenue for April to Oct in 2023-2024 was 10,511 crore. During the same period in 2024-2025, the revenue increased to 11,733 crore.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government to launch PMAY 2.0 for housing subsidies
news.para: Set to launch the second edition of the Prime Minister Awas Yojana (PMAY 2.0) the state and the centre would hold deliberations on the roadmap for delivery of houses to both urban poor and underprivileged families staying in the rural areas.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: City corporation to build residential complex for residents of Vikalanga colony
news.para: ​​This project marks a significant step toward improving housing for disabled community members who have been residing in the Vikalanga Colony for nearly five decades.

news.title: Goa: 30 illegal houses on government land demolished in Cunchelim
news.para: The land has been designated for a multi-faith burial ground and cemetery. Several individuals are accused of illegally occupying this land and building homes without permission.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh draft policy bars defaulters from bidding for group housing projects
news.para: The draft, currently being reviewed by the three development authorities, could help the three development authorities cumulatively facing Rs 40,000 crore in land dues turn the corner.

news.title: Court grants bail to Radius Group's MD in Yes Bank-DHFL fraud case
news.para: Radius Group's MD was arrested over two years ago in a money laundering case related to the Yes Bank-DHFL loan fraud. The court held that a speedy trial is a fundamental right.

news.title: Sebi issues Rs 52 crore demand notice to two entities in RHFL illegal fund diversion case
news.para: The regulator has warned these entities to attach assets and bank accounts if they fail to make the payment within 15 days.

news.title: Blox acquires 11% stake in property brokerage firm Guardians for $12 million
news.para: "This acquisition solidifies Blox and Guardians as India's largest real estate seller, managing annual sales of approximately 25,000 homes with a consolidated gross transaction value (GTV) of USD 2 billion in the primary residential market," Blox said.

news.title: Repco Home Finance's net profit up 14.51% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Repco Home Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 424.19 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 11.41 per cent from Rs 380.75 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Sunteck Realty posts net profit of Rs 34.62 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Sunteck Realty's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 182.05 crore in Q2 FY25 as against Rs 36.22 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Nexus Select Trust's net profit dips 56.16% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Nexus Select Trust's net operating income stood at Rs 3,713 million.  The board declared distributions of Rs 3,040.61 million / Rs 2.007 per unit for the quarter ended September 30, 2024.

news.title: Build Nivesh raises Rs 40 crore in maiden real estate AIF
news.para: "The fund has marked its final close with a total corpus of Rs 40 crore along with commitments of Rs 40 crore from its investors for add-on investment opportunities thereby augmenting the total investible corpus," it said.

news.title: Eldeco Housing & Industries' net profit dips 29.64% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Eldeco Housing & Industries' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 36.38 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 95.07 per cent from Rs 18.65 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kochi: Residents of Chander Kunj Army towers approach HC over irregularities in construction
news.para: Earlier, Indian Institute of Science Bengaluru (IISc), which carried out a review and structural assessment as per a Kerala high court order, recommended the demolition of the twin towers in the AWHO housing complex.

news.title: Shalimar Paints posts net loss of Rs 19.62 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Shalimar Paints' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 146.13 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 20.15 per cent from Rs 121.62 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Segro to buy six Tritax EuroBox properties for $499 million in deal with Brookfield
news.para: Segro's purchase comes weeks after the Canadian asset manager outbid the London-based warehousing specialist in the race to buy Tritax EuroBox in a 1.1 billion pound ($1.41 billion) deal, including debt.

news.title: Rajasthan government plans to develop hi-tech city near Jaipur
news.para: Recently, Boston Consulting Group – a multinational consulting firm – gave a presentation on the concept of hi-tech cities, follwing which the state govt has started looking for suitable land on outskirts of Jaipur.
